00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,200
Asia goes communist.

259
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:15,500
Eh-eh, now even George
all admits that.

260
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:18,300
Everybody else thinks we aught
to up the ante.

261
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:19,700
Bombing?

262
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:23,800
Look at this.

263
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:31,400
A bunch of sheds,
just outside on the water.

264
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,600
And they call that a military target.

265
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:35,500
There's school right up the street,

266
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:36,800
Poles built it for em.

267
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:40,300
Hell, Clark, I could build em a
thousand damn schools.

268
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:46,200
I'd like you to start to follow
the situation down there,

269
00:16:46,300 --> 00:16:48,800
read some of these reports
they keep throwin at me.

270
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:52,400
Eh, I just don't know what to believe
any more biggest damn mess.

271
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:55,600
And bein on the outside
you could take a fresh look.

272
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:58,400
I'll do everything I can to help.

273
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:00,300
Yeah, except come work for me.

274
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,600
Hey, what about the Supreme Court,

275
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:03,700
what if a seat opens up?

276
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:06,400
I'm an advocate, I'm not a judge.

277
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:09,600
Hell, Clark, you're a hick lawyer
from Missouri.

278
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:11,800
Well, I may be a hick lawyer
from Missouri,

279
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,800
But as you yourself pointed out
I haven't made

280
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,700
Missouri wages for a long, long time.

281
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:19,800
You know,

282
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:24,000
I ran sayin I was for peace,
now sure as hell,

283
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:27,000
they're tellin me I gotta do
what I said I wasn't gonna do.

284
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:29,600
What Goldwater was gonna do.

285
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:41,300
Luci's converting to Catholicism.

286
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:43,100
Big decision for a young girl.

287
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:47,000
He told me.
He said when the press gets wind

288
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,700
they'll make it sound
as if she did it

289
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:50,600
as a tribute to the Kennedy's.

290
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:54,700
I swear
I think he was only half joking.

291
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:01,500
Clark?

292
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:24,200
Hello? I'm sorry, he's asleep.

293
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:25,300
He just got over neumonia,

294
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,000
I'd rather not wake him.

295
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:30,900
I... I know, is it possible...

296
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:32,000
Marg?

297
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:38,500
Sorry, Bob, must be pretty damn bad
to keep you at home.

298
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,300
Let's just call it the Hanoi flu.

299
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:41,700
What the hell's goin on here?

300
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:42,600
General.

301
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:44,700
Corps Head Quarters at Pleiku.

302
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,500
Vietcong cut through the wire,

303
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:47,900
blew up our advisers barracks,

304
00:18:48,100 --> 00:18:50,800
planes and choppers on the runway
and Camp Holloway.

305
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:52,300
Casualty report.
More of the same,

306
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,700
advisers compound next door.

307
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,900
VC got in with mortar
and grenade launchers.

308
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:59,100
There are eight dead, a hundred
and twenty plus wounded,

309
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:01,600
six choppers, one transport destroyed
other aircraft severely damaged.

310
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:03,900
Mr. Secretary?

311
00:19:04,100 --> 00:19:07,100
The National Security Advisors
in Saigon, is he not?

312
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:10,500
Didn't the CIA say Hanoi
would connect Bundy's visit

313
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:11,900
with a decision on bombing?

314
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:13,300
Vietcong agents in Saigon government

315
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:14,500
probably leaked it out.

316
00:19:14,700 --> 00:19:18,300
And knowing this, knowing this look
what they did, Bob.

317
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:20,100
They blew up a hundred
and twentyeight people

318
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,800
just to thumb their noses at us.

319
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,100
Now what the hell
are we going to do about it?

320
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,300
Number 33, the North Vietnamese
barracks at

321
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:32,500
Dong Hoi just over the border
in North Vietnam,

322
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:34,300
about six thousand troops based there

323
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:36,900
An isolated facility
with minimal civilian support.

324
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,100
What are the expected casualties?

325
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:40,700
Thirty six hundred troops,
uh, roughly forty civilians.

326
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,200
How'd you come up with these numbers?

327
00:19:42,700 --> 00:19:46,000
Sir, we take the approach, look at
the blast pattern,

328
00:19:46,100 --> 00:19:49,100
size of the blast, demographics...

329
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:52,000
Mr. President, it's a sophisticated
an analysis as I've seen,

330
00:19:52,100 --> 00:19:54,500
unprecedented in aerial warfare.

331
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:57,500
Well, Ho Chi Minh's not gonna
turn tail overnight.

332
00:19:57,700 --> 00:20:00,500
Saigon's gonna take a shellackin
for anything we do.

333
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,400
And if they go
in now it'd be like sendin

334
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:05,200
in a widow woman to slap Jack Dempsey.

335
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:07,500
Sir, we doubt Hanoi will slap back.

336
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:09,000
Didn't MacArthur say the same thing

337
00:20:09,100 --> 00:20:11,600
when a million Chinese poured
into Korea?

338
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:16,100
What does State think of this?

339
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:20,200
The risk of inaction
means more aggression,

340
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:21,900
Ambassador Taylor concurs.

341
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,200
He's meeting
with Saigon's leaders now

342
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:26,300
and should be calling
the Situation Room momentarily.

343
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:27,900
They'll put him through to me.

344
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,500
Mr. President, if I might.

345
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:30,400
I was in charge of

346
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:32,500
bombing survey's during World War'II,

347
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:35,200
And bombing never wins a war.

348
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,700
Rather than erode the enemy's
will it strengthens it,

349
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,200
we've seen this time and time again,

350
00:20:39,300 --> 00:20:40,600
in the Blitz, Berlin.

351
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:42,000
Well, Blitz and Berlin
never woulda happened

352
00:20:42,100 --> 00:20:44,600
If we didn't lay down
to Hitler's Munich.

353
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:46,700
And if we lay down now it'll be
the same thing again.

354
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:49,300
An open invitation to more
of their aggression.

355
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:51,400
Mr. President, what we're proposing
with Rolling

356
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:54,800
Thunder is a strictly limited program
of sustained retaliation

357
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:58,300
moving Northward only if Vietcong act
vity persists.

358
00:20:58,400 --> 00:20:59,800
But it will persist, Bob.

359
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,500
We'll be bombing their cities
before we know it,

360
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:04,500
now do we expect Russia to sit still
for that? Or China?

361
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:08,800
Comparisons with Korea fifteen years
ago are flimsy at best, Mr. President.

362
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,000
You are absolutely right.

363
00:21:10,100 --> 00:21:11,800
China has atomic weapons now.

364
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:13,400
They tested their first bomb
four months ago,

365
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:16,600
it was no dud. We have no idea
what will set them off.

366
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:18,900
I, I don't understand.

367
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:20,400
Why is this?

368
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:24,500
North Vietnam has secret treaties
with the Chicoms, Mr. President.

369
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:26,500
We don't know what the flashpoints are

370
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,000
in their intervention.

371
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:30,600
We could take China out
in seventeen minutes.

372
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:32,500
They'd be crazy to take us on.

373
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:37,000
I agree, Bus, but why assume
they're as rational as we are?

374
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:40,300
Mr. President, four hundred Americans
have died in Vietnam,

375
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:43,000
and now eight more
in these atrocities,

376
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:45,800
there has to be a response
to this aggression.

377
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:46,700
Mr. President,

378
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,800
the Air Force
will be launching strikes

379
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,000
from the Danang airfield,

380
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:51,900
and that base will become

381
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:53,800
a more attractive target
to the Vietcong.

382
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:56,200
General Westmoreland is requesting
a Hawk missile battalion.

383
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,500
Is he asking for troops?

384
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,200
No. No troops.

385
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:01,700
Saigon will be responsible
for a base defense

386
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:05,300
but if the Vietcong activity
intensifies despite these measures,

387
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:06,500
they may need some help.

388
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,700
But it will intensify, Bob!

389
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:11,000
This is precisely my point,
Mr. President.

390
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:14,500
Yes?

391
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:17,600
Defense Secretary, Saigon,
Ambassador Taylor.

392
00:22:17,700 --> 00:22:18,900
Put him through.

393
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:22,200
Max, we're all here with President
Go ahead.

394
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:24,600
Mr. President, gentlemen,

395
00:22:24,700 --> 00:22:27,600
Saigon has agreed to the commencement
of air strikes.

396
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:31,000
They say their army's ready for any
counterattack from the North.

397
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,900
All right, Max. Thank you.

398
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:42,000
George... your concerns are mine,
as well as you know

399
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:44,800
but we're no where nea
the point you suggest,

400
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:46,500
and many here agree
there's a good chance

401
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:50,700
that Ho Chi Minh will quit
if we start makin him pay.

402
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:53,400
Now is there anyone here
who does not agree with this?

403
00:22:54,100 --> 00:22:55,300
I'm concerned about the press.

404
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:57,300
They're gonna view this
as a change in policy.

405
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:59,000
There is no change in policy.

406
00:22:59,100 --> 00:23:00,000
But we haven't struck back

407
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:02,100
since the Tonkin Gulf
affair six months ago.

408
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:02,800
That's right,

409
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:04,300
that's when I asked Congress
for the power,

410
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:06,300
they gave me the power,
now I'm usin it.

411
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:08,600
But we're takin it slow.

412
00:23:09,300 --> 00:23:11,200
I'm not goin to Hanoi.

413
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:15,700
And I'm signin off on every target.

414
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:18,100
You're not gonna bomb
the smallest outhouse

415
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:19,700
without checking with me.

416
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:21,200
You understand, General?

417
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:22,800
We understand, Mr. President.

418
00:23:23,500 --> 00:23:25,600
All right, Bob, you better get goin.

419
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:28,200
Now, anything else?

420
00:23:37,300 --> 00:23:39,200
From Robert'S. McNamara

421
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:43,700
to Admiral U.S. Grant Sharp, Commander
Pacific Forces, Honolulu.

422
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:45,800
This is an execution order.

423
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:49,400
During daylight hours,
7 February 1965, Saigon time,

424
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:52,400
conduct the following
coordinated attacks:

425
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:55,600
Number 33 X Dong Hoi barracks...

426
00:24:07,900 --> 00:24:09,400
Good evening, Mr. President.

427
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:10,800
Planes back?

428
00:24:10,900 --> 00:24:12,800
Uh, the carriers weren't on station
when the order went out, sir.

429
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:14,400
The operation has been delayed.

430
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:15,500
Delayed?

431
00:24:15,700 --> 00:24:17,900
About ninety minutes, sir.
We should have word shortly.

432
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,000
At ease.

433
00:24:47,300 --> 00:24:48,300
What happened?

434
00:24:48,500 --> 00:24:49,600
It's monsoon season there, sir.

435
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:51,600
Well are they goin
or aren't they goin !?

436
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:53,800
You find out what the hell's goin on
and you call me.

437
00:24:53,900 --> 00:24:55,700
Get the White House operator
to put you through.

438
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:56,600
You want me to wake you, sir?

439
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:58,000
You won't wake me!

440
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:07,700
Why you up?

441
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:08,900
Worried for you.

442
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:13,000
Those planes
should a been back hours ago.

443
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:15,400
What's that?

444
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:18,000
Letter from a friend complainin
about junkyards.

445
00:25:20,800 --> 00:25:22,200
She says here...

446
00:25:23,300 --> 00:25:25,600
they're all up
and down the highway now

447
00:25:25,700 --> 00:25:28,800
through Dallas to San Antonio
and Houston to Austin...

448
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:31,000
Right on the highway
or away where people can't see?

449
00:25:31,100 --> 00:25:33,600
No, right along the road defilin
the countryside.

450
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:37,100
Through Waxahachie and Hillboro,

451
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:39,700
and lovely San Marcos
where you went to school.

452
00:25:39,900 --> 00:25:44,000
Oh. Love... don't.... Love.

453
00:25:47,300 --> 00:25:48,600
Yes, Mr. President?

454
00:25:48,700 --> 00:25:51,000
What are you do in about junkyards
on the highways?

455
00:25:51,100 --> 00:25:52,700
What?
Junkyards!

456
00:25:52,900 --> 00:25:54,800
Well, I'm sendin somethin over to
your office right now.

457
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:58,100
You jump in your car in your jammies
you might even beat it.

458
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:02,100
Yes?

459
00:26:02,300 --> 00:26:04,900
I spoke with Honolulu,
they're cabling now.

460
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:08,100
Planes are back, the primary was hit.

461
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:09,900
All the planes, they all get back?

462
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:12,300
Uh, no, sir.
I'm afraid we did lose one plane.

463
00:26:14,100 --> 00:26:15,400
What about the pilot?

464
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:16,800
He went down at sea,

465
00:26:16,900 --> 00:26:18,700
Search and Rescue
is looking for him now

466
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:20,700
but I'm afraid it's not looking
very good.

467
00:26:20,900 --> 00:26:22,500
I'm sorry, sir.

468
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:24,900
All right, thank you, Bob.

469
00:26:25,100 --> 00:26:26,500
Good night, Mr. President.

470
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:28,600
Yes, Mr. President?

471
00:26:31,100 --> 00:26:32,400
Lyndon.

472
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:35,800
Oh, I'm sorry.

473
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:40,000
Put this on Moyer's desk.

474
00:26:40,100 --> 00:26:41,200
Yes, sir.

475
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:47,700
Honey?

476
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:50,300
We lost a pilot.

477
00:26:51,900 --> 00:26:53,400
Sweetheart.

478
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:59,800
Sweetheart. Oh, I'm so sorry.

479
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:07,500
This isn't about junkyards, is it?

480
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,600
Shit, what time is it?

481
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:15,900
I told Sandra I'd be home before one.

482
00:27:18,500 --> 00:27:20,100
She didn't call.

483
00:27:20,500 --> 00:27:22,100
That's not a good sign.

484
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:27,900
What about you, you coming or going?

485
00:27:28,500 --> 00:27:29,700
He wants company.

486
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:34,500
We started bombing
North Vietnam tonight.

487
00:27:35,300 --> 00:27:40,700
Christ. Are they talking about
combat troops?

488
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:43,100
No. Not yet.

489
00:27:43,300 --> 00:27:45,000
No.

490
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:47,900
Christ,
I don't know what to tell the press.

491
00:27:48,900 --> 00:27:51,400
We are backing into a war here,
for Christ's sake

492
00:27:51,500 --> 00:27:53,900
and it's a war he campaigned against.

493
00:27:54,300 --> 00:27:56,600
But now,
he talks like he's puttin a paddle

494
00:27:56,700 --> 00:27:58,600
to Ho Chi Minh's behind.

495
00:27:59,100 --> 00:28:00,900
Nah, Johnson's a deal maker.

496
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:03,400
He's the best politician
this country's ever seen,

497
00:28:03,500 --> 00:28:05,100
he'll find a way out of this.

498
00:28:06,300 --> 00:28:09,200
Sure, we'll just get
old Uncle Ho down to the ranch,

499
00:28:09,300 --> 00:28:11,800
serve him up some tasty barbecue

500
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:13,000
and then offer him a damn.

501
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:14,600
Or a Federal Judgeship.

502
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:16,400
Hello, Mr. President.

503
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:18,200
Good evening, Mr. President.

504
00:28:18,300 --> 00:28:21,000
Congratulations on getting
that education bill out of committee.

505
00:28:21,100 --> 00:28:22,300
Well, it hasn't passed yet, has it?

506
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:24,300
I want all ya up there
on the hill day and night

507
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:25,700
to get me those yeas.

508
00:28:26,700 --> 00:28:27,700
What is this?

509
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:28,900
Tapioca puddin ?

510
00:28:29,100 --> 00:28:30,100
Yes, sir.

511
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:32,200
Would you like it?

512
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:35,100
Ah, now, votin rights,

513
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:37,700
that's the meat in the coconut, boys.
Where do we stand?

514
00:28:37,900 --> 00:28:40,800
Um, at last tally
we are short fifty congressmen.

