00:45:42,500 --> 00:45:44,500
this is just a continuation
of the war with the French,

823
00:45:44,700 --> 00:45:45,400
and the Japanese,

824
00:45:45,500 --> 00:45:48,500
and the Chinese a thousand years
before that.

825
00:45:48,700 --> 00:45:49,800
We never should have allowed
the French

826
00:45:49,900 --> 00:45:52,100
to reclaim their colonies in 45,

827
00:45:52,200 --> 00:45:53,700
but we needed them aligned with us

828
00:45:53,900 --> 00:45:57,100
against the Soviets and that
was their price.

829
00:45:57,600 --> 00:45:59,300
Will we end up like the French?

830
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:03,400
A great power cuttin and runnin from
a bunch a little men in black pajamas,

831
00:46:03,600 --> 00:46:05,300
tuckin our tail in defeat?

832
00:46:06,600 --> 00:46:08,400
France didn't have the fire power
we have.

833
00:46:08,600 --> 00:46:11,000
But the bombing seems
to have no affect.

834
00:46:11,100 --> 00:46:12,700
Well, it appears now
that it won't stop them,

835
00:46:12,900 --> 00:46:15,200
but it has slowed down their resupply.

836
00:46:15,400 --> 00:46:17,400
Hanoi's starting
to send down large units

837
00:46:17,500 --> 00:46:18,800
and the more of
their men we can tie up

838
00:46:18,900 --> 00:46:20,600
with repairing roads and bridges,

839
00:46:20,800 --> 00:46:22,800
the fewer they can spare
to fight the South.

840
00:46:26,100 --> 00:46:27,800
What do we have there now?

841
00:46:28,800 --> 00:46:32,200
Well, we've got the 3rd Marines
at Danang, Phu Bai,

842
00:46:32,300 --> 00:46:34,900
Chu Lai, the 173rd Airborne
at Vung Tau,

843
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:37,100
for base defense and support
of the South Vietnamese

844
00:46:37,200 --> 00:46:38,600
units 13 battalions in all.

845
00:46:38,800 --> 00:46:41,100
Never mind battalions, how many boys?

846
00:46:42,100 --> 00:46:44,400
Fifty-one thousand troops,
Mr. President.

847
00:46:44,600 --> 00:46:46,800
Yeah, and Westmorel
and wants how many?

848
00:46:53,600 --> 00:46:55,500
One hundred eighty-four thousand.

849
00:46:56,400 --> 00:46:58,300
And the authority to launch
offensive operations

850
00:46:58,400 --> 00:46:59,800
under his own command.

851
00:47:03,900 --> 00:47:06,000
The South Vietnamese are useless,
Mr. President.

852
00:47:06,200 --> 00:47:08,000
They've lost four battalions
in a month.

853
00:47:08,200 --> 00:47:09,600
Desertions are at record levels.

854
00:47:09,800 --> 00:47:11,200
They're losing
and they're losing fast.

855
00:47:11,400 --> 00:47:12,400
National Security Advisor
I know they're losin !

856
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:15,300
I don't need a Phi Beta Kappa key
to know they're losin !

857
00:47:15,400 --> 00:47:17,500
Anyone smart enough to pour piss
out of a boot

858
00:47:17,700 --> 00:47:19,100
knows they're losin !

859
00:47:25,700 --> 00:47:28,300
How many casualties
you think we'll take?

860
00:47:32,200 --> 00:47:34,700
We could reach 500 a month
by the end of the year

861
00:47:34,800 --> 00:47:36,500
if Hanoi hasn't quit by then.

862
00:47:37,600 --> 00:47:39,400
Five hundred a month?

863
00:47:41,400 --> 00:47:43,200
You tell Westmorel that
he's got the authority.

864
00:47:43,400 --> 00:47:45,400
Tell him to get out there
and kill Vietcong,

865
00:47:45,600 --> 00:47:47,500
and do whatever he has
to do to hold em off.

866
00:47:47,600 --> 00:47:49,300
Then you and Wheeler go and see him

867
00:47:49,500 --> 00:47:50,600
and nail him down on what he needs

868
00:47:50,700 --> 00:47:52,500
to get this thing over with.

869
00:47:52,600 --> 00:47:55,300
Then damn it, let's get it over with!

870
00:47:57,200 --> 00:48:00,500
U.S. Command Center, Saigon

871
00:48:00,600 --> 00:48:02,400
Kid was setting fuses
on the goddamn bridge,

872
00:48:02,600 --> 00:48:03,600
do you believe it?

873
00:48:03,700 --> 00:48:05,200
I was five minutes away.

874
00:48:05,300 --> 00:48:07,200
And that potshot last time I was here

875
00:48:07,300 --> 00:48:08,300
he missed me by a mile.

876
00:48:08,500 --> 00:48:12,100
Jesus, you'd think they'd put their
best sniper on the job.

877
00:48:12,200 --> 00:48:13,000
I wish I could tell you

878
00:48:13,100 --> 00:48:15,700
they were representative of the enemy
Mr. Secretary.

879
00:48:19,300 --> 00:48:23,200
My strategy for the war is divided
into three phases.

880
00:48:23,300 --> 00:48:24,300
In Phase I,

881
00:48:24,500 --> 00:48:27,900
employing the 184,000 man level
now being considered,

882
00:48:28,100 --> 00:48:31,200
we would halt the losing trend
by the end of 1965.

883
00:48:32,100 --> 00:48:33,400
In Phase II,

884
00:48:33,500 --> 00:48:37,200
for which an additional
100,000 troops would be needed,

885
00:48:37,300 --> 00:48:42,300
allied forces would gain
the initiative by June 30, 1966,

886
00:48:42,400 --> 00:48:44,600
pacification activities
would be expanded

887
00:48:44,700 --> 00:48:47,700
aimed at winning the hearts and minds

888
00:48:47,900 --> 00:48:50,900
of the South Vietnamese peasantry.

889
00:48:51,000 --> 00:48:53,200
If the Communists do not then give up

890
00:48:53,300 --> 00:48:57,000
Phase III of our strategy would kick
in the win phase,

891
00:48:57,100 --> 00:48:59,800
which would being on July 1, 1966

892
00:48:59,900 --> 00:49:04,000
and conclude by December 31, 1967

893
00:49:04,200 --> 00:49:08,000
the defeat of remaining
enemy forces and base areas.

894
00:49:08,100 --> 00:49:11,400
Additional reinforcements
will be needed for this phase,

895
00:49:11,500 --> 00:49:15,100
following which allied forces
will begin to be withdrawn.

896
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:18,200
General, that's a marvelous plan,

897
00:49:18,700 --> 00:49:21,300
but uh, excessively abstract.

898
00:49:21,400 --> 00:49:22,800
I want to see your numbers.

899
00:49:23,500 --> 00:49:25,900
I want to see the percentage
of the country you now control,

900
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:27,300
The percentage intend to control

901
00:49:27,500 --> 00:49:29,900
with these 200,000 additional men.

902
00:49:30,300 --> 00:49:32,700
I want to see rates of infiltration
and interdiction,

903
00:49:32,800 --> 00:49:35,300
force ratios in each
of the tactical corps zones

904
00:49:35,400 --> 00:49:37,700
and enemy casualties
in battles fought

905
00:49:37,800 --> 00:49:41,000
and projected battles
against these added forces.

906
00:50:00,700 --> 00:50:02,800
Mr. Clifford, The President
on Line One.

907
00:50:03,300 --> 00:50:05,800
Old friend, I need you here.

908
00:50:14,400 --> 00:50:16,600
Whatever resources are lost through
bombing or capture,

909
00:50:16,800 --> 00:50:18,600
China and Russia will make up
with resupply,

910
00:50:18,800 --> 00:50:19,500
encouraging a friendly game

911
00:50:19,600 --> 00:50:21,600
of I'm more revolutionary than though

912
00:50:21,800 --> 00:50:23,900
Our intervention
will give them a cause

913
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:26,100
over which to unite when it is
in our interest to deepen

914
00:50:26,300 --> 00:50:27,300
the breach between them.

915
00:50:27,400 --> 00:50:29,200
Wouldn't we lose credibility
throughout the world

916
00:50:29,300 --> 00:50:30,600
if we give up as you propose?

917
00:50:30,700 --> 00:50:32,600
Wouldn t this be an irreparable
blow, George?

918
00:50:32,800 --> 00:50:33,700
A worse blow, Mr. President,

919
00:50:33,900 --> 00:50:36,900
would be that the mightiest
power in the world is unable to defeat

920
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:38,100
one of the most backward.

