00:50:43,800 --> 00:50:45,700
But can we get the job done?

925
00:50:46,200 --> 00:50:48,100
What if they put their stack in?

926
00:50:48,300 --> 00:50:49,900
What makes you think
if we put in the numbers

927
00:50:50,000 --> 00:50:53,300
you're suggesting that Ho Chi Minh
won't match us man for man?

928
00:50:53,400 --> 00:50:55,800
This means greater bodies of men,
Mr. President,

929
00:50:56,000 --> 00:50:57,700
Which will allow us to cream them.

930
00:50:57,800 --> 00:50:59,600
Their firepower against ours...

931
00:50:59,700 --> 00:51:02,100
Why does anyone think
that they will accommodate us

932
00:51:02,300 --> 00:51:03,600
by fighting our kind of war?

933
00:51:03,700 --> 00:51:05,000
Their tactics are terror,

934
00:51:05,100 --> 00:51:08,000
and sniping they have better
access to intelligence.

935
00:51:08,400 --> 00:51:09,800
Why is this?

936
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:12,600
It's because the South Vietnamese
government is heavily

937
00:51:12,700 --> 00:51:15,200
infiltrated with Vietcong agents,
Mr. President.

938
00:51:16,800 --> 00:51:18,600
What other road can we go,
negotiations,

939
00:51:18,700 --> 00:51:19,900
stopping the bombing?

940
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:22,200
These make us look weak,
with cup in hand.

941
00:51:22,400 --> 00:51:25,000
Better to lose now than
after committing 200,000 men.

942
00:51:25,100 --> 00:51:27,700
I disagree. We have to make
a stand here,

943
00:51:27,900 --> 00:51:29,800
and if we fail it
could be chalked up to

944
00:51:30,000 --> 00:51:31,200
any number of things corruption

945
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:32,700
amongst Saigon's leaders for instance,

946
00:51:32,800 --> 00:51:33,900
then we can get out.

947
00:51:34,100 --> 00:51:36,100
But this government would have stood
up to the Communists.

948
00:51:36,200 --> 00:51:39,300
But we won't get out,
Bob, we will double our bet

949
00:51:39,400 --> 00:51:40,900
and get massacred in the rice paddies

950
00:51:41,000 --> 00:51:44,200
So-so-so-so, what's you're advice,
George? Cut and run?

951
00:51:45,800 --> 00:51:47,100
Mr. President,

952
00:51:48,900 --> 00:51:51,400
no great captain in history
ever hesitated

953
00:51:51,500 --> 00:51:53,700
to make a tactical withdrawal
when conditions were

954
00:51:53,900 --> 00:51:55,200
unfavorable to him.

955
00:51:59,400 --> 00:52:01,900
Does anyone else here agree
with what George is sayin ?

956
00:52:06,300 --> 00:52:08,300
I've asked Clark Clifford to join us.

957
00:52:09,500 --> 00:52:12,900
Clark, you have any comments
at this time?

958
00:52:15,100 --> 00:52:18,400
I, I have a question
for General Wheeler.

959
00:52:18,500 --> 00:52:19,600
Yes, sir.

960
00:52:19,700 --> 00:52:20,600
Good morning, General.

