00:54:49,400 --> 00:54:51,000
Well, I hate sendin ya.

1018
00:54:51,100 --> 00:54:53,100
The whole thing stinks to high heaven

1019
00:54:54,100 --> 00:54:56,100
What'd you wanna tell me in private?

1020
00:54:59,300 --> 00:55:02,400
I've managed to keep
these Vietnam expenditures

1021
00:55:02,500 --> 00:55:03,800
under wraps as you requested,

1022
00:55:03,900 --> 00:55:05,800
but if you decide
to move forward with this,

1023
00:55:05,900 --> 00:55:09,000
it's going to be impossible to keep up
the guise indefinitely

1024
00:55:09,200 --> 00:55:11,300
and I strongly believe
you should present

1025
00:55:11,400 --> 00:55:13,300
this bill to the American people.
No, absolutely not.

1026
00:55:13,400 --> 00:55:14,200
Mr. President,

1027
00:55:14,300 --> 00:55:17,300
I can't continue to hide
these kinds of figures.

1028
00:55:17,400 --> 00:55:19,700
Phase I of Westmoreland's
program alone

1029
00:55:19,800 --> 00:55:22,800
is going to run us
twelve billion dollars.

1030
00:55:22,900 --> 00:55:24,900
Twelve billion!?

1031
00:55:25,300 --> 00:55:28,100
I can't ask Congress
for twelve billion dollars!

1032
00:55:28,300 --> 00:55:29,800
Mr. President.
Bob, it'll be unshirted hell

1033
00:55:29,900 --> 00:55:32,400
if I go to the Hill askin for
that kind of money.

1034
00:55:32,500 --> 00:55:34,600
I'll never get another thing
out of em again.

1035
00:55:34,700 --> 00:55:36,500
Now how much can you trim off that?

1036
00:55:38,500 --> 00:55:40,800
Bob, I've got my ox in a ditch here.

1037
00:55:41,300 --> 00:55:42,500
Now, what can you do for me?

1038
00:55:44,200 --> 00:55:46,300
If we continue to use
the maximum transfer authority

1039
00:55:46,400 --> 00:55:47,300
from other areas,

1040
00:55:47,500 --> 00:55:48,600
I could probably
cut these figures in half,

1041
00:55:48,800 --> 00:55:49,900
but we'd still
need a big appropriation

1042
00:55:50,100 --> 00:55:51,900
to carry us through this year.

1043
00:55:52,600 --> 00:55:54,800
But Westmoreland says
if we put the men in,

1044
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:56,600
there's a chance they'll quit
by year's end, right?

1045
00:55:56,800 --> 00:55:57,900
Well, that's certainly
what we all hope,

1046
00:55:58,100 --> 00:55:59,000
but we can't count on West...

1047
00:55:59,100 --> 00:56:01,000
You just do the number countin,
will ya, Bob?

1048
00:56:01,100 --> 00:56:01,600
Yeah.

1049
00:56:01,700 --> 00:56:03,100
Get as low as you can.

1050
00:56:05,600 --> 00:56:06,500
One more.

1051
00:56:10,700 --> 00:56:12,700
All right. All right, thank you,
thank you.

1052
00:56:15,400 --> 00:56:17,600
Dick,
I need a statement for next week.

1053
00:56:17,700 --> 00:56:19,100
I'm not sure yet
if I'm gonna want to use it,

1054
00:56:19,300 --> 00:56:20,100
but I need it ready.

1055
00:56:20,200 --> 00:56:21,500
All right, Mr. President.

1056
00:56:21,700 --> 00:56:23,700
You know, Jack,
I want war like I want polio

1057
00:56:23,900 --> 00:56:27,100
the shootin, the bombin goes against
every bone in my body.

1058
00:56:27,300 --> 00:56:29,500
You know
that better than almost anyone.

1059
00:56:29,700 --> 00:56:30,800
These young people here,

1060
00:56:30,900 --> 00:56:32,500
that's what I'm all about.

1061
00:56:32,600 --> 00:56:33,800
That was me,

1062
00:56:33,900 --> 00:56:36,400
in Cotulla teachin Mexican kids
livin in hovels,

1063
00:56:36,500 --> 00:56:39,700
treated worse than you'd treat a dog.

1064
00:56:39,900 --> 00:56:42,300
But here I start
a billion dollar bank

1065
00:56:42,500 --> 00:56:44,200
for em in Southeast Asia, free money,

1066
00:56:44,300 --> 00:56:46,400
and Ho Chi Minh wants no part of it.

1067
00:56:46,500 --> 00:56:49,100
I could a turned that place
into the Tennessee Valley.

1068
00:56:49,300 --> 00:56:51,300
I read he said he's willin to fight
for twenty years.

1069
00:56:51,500 --> 00:56:52,700
I know what he says
and I know what I say

1070
00:56:52,800 --> 00:56:56,200
and I know what I must do despite
what I say, damn it!

1071
00:56:57,100 --> 00:57:00,200
I want to leave the footprint
of America in Vietnam,

1072
00:57:00,300 --> 00:57:03,000
schools, dams, hospitals.

1073
00:57:03,100 --> 00:57:05,400
Bomb craters that'll be our footprint

1074
00:57:05,500 --> 00:57:07,200
That's what they'll remember me for.

1075
00:57:07,800 --> 00:57:10,000
Not civil rights or health care
or education.

1076
00:57:10,100 --> 00:57:13,400
No, sir,
it'll be Vietnam, Vietnam, Vietnam.

1077
00:57:13,900 --> 00:57:16,000
Twenty bills I'm tryin to get out
of committee,

1078
00:57:16,100 --> 00:57:18,400
and twelve outta eighteen
workin hours everyday,

1079
00:57:18,500 --> 00:57:22,200
my head's stuck up that raggedy-ass
little fourth-rate country

1080
00:57:22,300 --> 00:57:24,600
that doesn't even have the fight
to save itself.

1081
00:57:29,200 --> 00:57:31,800
You get with McNamara,
you know what it's gotta say

1082
00:57:32,000 --> 00:57:33,400
and tell Buzzby or Goodwin

1083
00:57:33,400 --> 00:57:34,800
we gotta put the music to it, Jack.

1084
00:57:47,100 --> 00:57:48,400
Why you up?

1085
00:57:48,900 --> 00:57:50,700
You needn't ask me that each time.

1086
00:57:50,800 --> 00:57:53,200
Ah, I tried not awake ya.

1087
00:57:54,000 --> 00:57:56,000
I got the ringer so low
I can't hear it,

1088
00:57:56,200 --> 00:57:57,500
and I got the flashlight.

1089
00:57:58,200 --> 00:58:00,400
Maybe you oughta sleep in
that other room you set up.

1090
00:58:01,400 --> 00:58:03,700
What happened to that Prime Rib
from the Medicare meetin ?

1091
00:58:03,800 --> 00:58:04,700
Is that what you want?

1092
00:58:04,800 --> 00:58:07,400
There's a nice chicken left
from the Education Lunch.

1093
00:58:07,500 --> 00:58:08,900
I saw em put it away.

1094
00:58:10,700 --> 00:58:12,700
Oh, darlin you been so good
about your diet,

1095
00:58:12,900 --> 00:58:14,100
I don't see any point
in the middle of the night...

1096
00:58:14,200 --> 00:58:15,600
I don't care about that now!

1097
00:58:16,100 --> 00:58:18,600
Another heart attack might
be the answer to my problems.

1098
00:58:19,100 --> 00:58:21,200
All right,
you stop that kinda talk please,

1099
00:58:21,300 --> 00:58:22,400
I worry enough about your health.

1100
00:58:22,500 --> 00:58:24,600
I'll fix somethin for you
if you sit down.

1101
00:58:24,800 --> 00:58:26,300
All right.
Come on.

1102
00:58:26,400 --> 00:58:27,400
All right.

1103
00:58:28,700 --> 00:58:29,800
I'm sorry.

1104
00:58:40,800 --> 00:58:42,200
Luci met a boy.

1105
00:58:43,400 --> 00:58:46,200
When she went on that Chicago trip
with you last week.

1106
00:58:46,300 --> 00:58:47,900
What do you mean she met a boy!?

1107
00:58:48,500 --> 00:58:50,200
Why didn't I know about this?

1108
00:58:50,400 --> 00:58:51,800
That day she went to Milwaukee

1109
00:58:52,000 --> 00:58:54,200
and visited the William Feldsteins.

1110
00:58:55,400 --> 00:58:59,000
She visited Beth Jenkins at Marquette

1111
00:58:59,100 --> 00:59:01,000
and Beth had some friends over,

1112
00:59:01,200 --> 00:59:05,500
all the students there
and among them was this...

1113
00:59:05,700 --> 00:59:10,200
boy, Patrick Nugent is his name.

1114
00:59:12,100 --> 00:59:13,500
He's Catholic.

1115
00:59:14,600 --> 00:59:17,900
Luci will only date boys
who are Catholic now

1116
00:59:18,500 --> 00:59:21,100
and she calls him Paddy.

1117
00:59:21,200 --> 00:59:21,700
Thank you.

1118
00:59:21,900 --> 00:59:23,600
So I am payin attention.

1119
00:59:24,400 --> 00:59:27,100
He's just tons, mother.

1120
00:59:27,700 --> 00:59:31,300
She said to me.
That's the new expression, tons.

1121
00:59:31,400 --> 00:59:32,400
Move your elbow.

1122
00:59:33,100 --> 00:59:33,800
Thank you.

1123
00:59:33,900 --> 00:59:36,200
Yeah. You like the chicken?

1124
00:59:36,900 --> 00:59:38,300
You remarked on it.

1125
00:59:41,200 --> 00:59:42,700
I didn't know of it.

1126
00:59:43,300 --> 00:59:45,200
You might have shown it
to me this mornin .

1127
00:59:46,500 --> 00:59:47,600
And woken you again?

1128
00:59:47,800 --> 00:59:48,900
Oh.

1129
00:59:49,300 --> 00:59:51,500
Like a jack ass in a hailstorm.

1130
00:59:52,100 --> 00:59:54,800
I guess I'll just have to hunker up
and take it.

1131
00:59:57,500 --> 01:00:00,000
I feel like I'm goin down in a plane,

1132
01:00:00,900 --> 01:00:05,500
and I can crash with it and burn up,
or jump and die.

1133
01:00:07,700 --> 01:00:11,500
Where we were when I came in,
I, I'd trade back to that.

1134
01:00:13,700 --> 01:00:16,500
I'd trade back
to the damn vice-presidency

1135
01:00:16,700 --> 01:00:18,600
to get outta this mess.

1136
01:00:30,400 --> 01:00:32,700
Clark, the President would like you
and your wife

1137
01:00:32,900 --> 01:00:34,200
to join him
at Camp David this weekend.

1138
01:00:34,300 --> 01:00:36,100
Oh, thank you, Bill.
Thank the President.

1139
01:00:36,200 --> 01:00:38,600
We'd love to,
but we have a prior engagement.

1140
01:00:38,700 --> 01:00:40,900
Clark,
is there anyway you can make it?

1141
01:00:41,000 --> 01:00:43,000
He's working on an escalation speech?

1142
01:00:43,100 --> 01:00:44,800
Has he made up his mind?

1143
01:00:45,000 --> 01:00:47,800
I'd say he has
but he's asking for you.

1144
01:00:47,900 --> 01:00:49,800
And who else will be there?

1145
01:00:49,900 --> 01:00:51,200
Bob McNamara.

1146
01:01:16,300 --> 01:01:17,300
Bob.

1147
01:01:20,400 --> 01:01:21,200
Mr. and Mrs. McNamara,

1148
01:01:21,300 --> 01:01:23,200
I'd like you to meet my friend,
Pat Nugent.

1149
01:01:23,700 --> 01:01:24,600
It's an honor to meet you, sir.

1150
01:01:24,700 --> 01:01:25,600
Pleasure. My wife, Marg.

1151
01:01:25,800 --> 01:01:26,900
Nice to meet you.

1152
01:01:27,100 --> 01:01:28,700
You're in National Guard,
where you stationed?

1153
01:01:28,800 --> 01:01:30,600
I'll be at Andrews with the 113th,
sir,

1154
01:01:30,800 --> 01:01:32,800
but down to San Antonio first
for basic.

1155
01:01:33,000 --> 01:01:34,600
Ah, Lackland Air Force Base, sure.

1156
01:01:34,800 --> 01:01:36,800
Used to call it Kelly back in 42
when I was goin

1157
01:01:37,000 --> 01:01:39,000
around helpin to build an Air Force
in this country.

1158
01:01:39,200 --> 01:01:40,600
You know,
we only had a handful of planes

1159
01:01:40,700 --> 01:01:41,600
when the Japanese attacked us,

1160
01:01:41,800 --> 01:01:43,300
spread all over the country.

1161
01:01:43,400 --> 01:01:45,000
Is that right?

1162
01:01:45,100 --> 01:01:46,800
And Hap Arnold knew
every one of em by name.

1163
01:01:47,000 --> 01:01:49,000
I have some Hap Arnold stories
for you.

1164
01:01:50,700 --> 01:01:53,500
Uh, sorry,
we'll leave everything till tomorrow,

1165
01:01:53,600 --> 01:01:54,300
we'll talk in the morning.

1166
01:01:54,400 --> 01:01:56,000
I look forward to it.
Come on in.

1167
01:02:00,500 --> 01:02:02,800
Let the best minds
of our administration

1168
01:02:03,000 --> 01:02:04,800
start looking for a way out

1169
01:02:05,000 --> 01:02:08,600
and stop looking for a way to win
this unwinnable war,

1170
01:02:08,700 --> 01:02:11,200
because it is my considered opinion,

1171
01:02:11,600 --> 01:02:13,900
that continuing on that path

1172
01:02:14,000 --> 01:02:19,800
will lead us to catastrophe.

1173
01:02:20,000 --> 01:02:23,400
Any unbiased jury would
give you your verdict, Clark,

1174
01:02:23,500 --> 01:02:24,900
no question.

1175
01:02:25,000 --> 01:02:26,200
Good.

1176
01:02:26,700 --> 01:02:30,500
But, if it's true what Moyer says;

1177
01:02:30,600 --> 01:02:33,300
that Lyndon's in McNamara's pocket...

1178
01:02:37,200 --> 01:02:40,100
McNamara has such sway in there.

1179
01:02:40,900 --> 01:02:44,500
Truman took your advice over
George Marshalls, for heaven sakes

1180
01:02:44,700 --> 01:02:46,300
Kennedy, too.

1181
01:02:46,400 --> 01:02:49,000
Yeah,
but Lyndon is another kettle of fish.

1182
01:02:50,100 --> 01:02:53,900
Give him a new vision,
Clark. He'll hear you.

1183
01:02:56,100 --> 01:02:57,800
Rinaldo, leave it there.

1184
01:03:04,500 --> 01:03:06,900
So, these are the numbers.

1185
01:03:07,100 --> 01:03:08,900
Now, you will not be held accountable

1186
01:03:09,100 --> 01:03:11,100
for anything that has happened up
till this point,

1187
01:03:11,300 --> 01:03:14,700
in fact, you will be admired
for the noble attempt

1188
01:03:14,800 --> 01:03:16,000
you have made
to honor your predecessor's

1189
01:03:16,100 --> 01:03:19,900
commitment a commitment
that has been exploited by

1190
01:03:20,000 --> 01:03:23,700
that corrupt and self-destructive
regime in South Vietnam.

1191
01:03:24,400 --> 01:03:27,300
The bombing might have worked,
but it hasn't.

1192
01:03:27,500 --> 01:03:28,700
And to make it work,

1193
01:03:28,800 --> 01:03:31,900
you would have to resort
to unconscionable measures

1194
01:03:32,000 --> 01:03:34,300
that would make you a her
to those in this country

1195
01:03:34,400 --> 01:03:38,500
you distain and a criminal
to those you have sought

1196
01:03:38,600 --> 01:03:41,000
all your life to assist
the young and the poor,

1197
01:03:41,500 --> 01:03:43,800
who are the ones
who will have to fight this war.

1198
01:03:44,000 --> 01:03:48,100
This, this is not the last inning
in the struggle against Communism.

1199
01:03:48,200 --> 01:03:50,100
We must pick those spots

1200
01:03:50,200 --> 01:03:52,000
where the stakes are highest for us

1201
01:03:52,200 --> 01:03:53,100
and where we hold the cards

1202
01:03:53,300 --> 01:03:56,000
that'll give us the greatest
opportunity to prevail.

1203
01:03:56,500 --> 01:03:58,800
Ho Chi Minh told the French,

1204
01:03:58,900 --> 01:04:02,300
he said, You will kill ten of my men

1205
01:04:02,400 --> 01:04:04,700
and I will kill only one of yours,

1206
01:04:04,800 --> 01:04:07,900
but in the end, it is you who'll tire.

1207
01:04:08,100 --> 01:04:09,800
And they did, and eleven years ago,

1208
01:04:09,900 --> 01:04:12,500
at the end they just couldn't do it
any more.

1209
01:04:12,600 --> 01:04:16,500
The North Vietnamese lost 500,000
in their war against the French

1210
01:04:16,700 --> 01:04:17,800
and they did not tire,

1211
01:04:17,900 --> 01:04:19,300
and they will not tire now.

1212
01:04:19,500 --> 01:04:21,500
Not after you commit a 100,000,

1213
01:04:21,600 --> 01:04:23,300
not after you commit 500,000.

1214
01:04:23,400 --> 01:04:27,300
And if you do not win decisively
after a big buildup,

1215
01:04:27,500 --> 01:04:29,500
it will be a huge catastrophe.

1216
01:04:30,000 --> 01:04:33,300
It will destroy
the American people's faith in you

1217
01:04:33,400 --> 01:04:36,000
and the democratic party
and their government

1218
01:04:36,200 --> 01:04:37,700
for years to come.

1219
01:04:38,200 --> 01:04:40,800
Now, you have always stressed
the economic

1220
01:04:41,000 --> 01:04:43,300
and social dimensions
of world problems.

1221
01:04:43,400 --> 01:04:45,300
And in this you are unrivaled.

1222
01:04:45,400 --> 01:04:47,900
You have a unique opportunity here

1223
01:04:48,000 --> 01:04:49,600
to address this problem,

1224
01:04:49,800 --> 01:04:51,600
economically and socially.

1225
01:04:51,800 --> 01:04:54,900
Not by war, not by killing people,

1226
01:04:55,300 --> 01:04:58,200
but by helping them here and there.

1227
01:04:58,800 --> 01:05:03,500
This is a year of minimum political
risk for you, Mr. President.

1228
01:05:03,600 --> 01:05:07,400
You were elected by the largest
landslide in our history,

1229
01:05:07,500 --> 01:05:09,600
the reactionary elements
of this society

1230
01:05:09,800 --> 01:05:11,900
will not soon recover

1231
01:05:12,000 --> 01:05:16,000
I foresee little erosion
of your prestige and power

1232
01:05:16,200 --> 01:05:19,900
if we cut our loses
and get out of Vietnam.

1233
01:05:20,900 --> 01:05:23,200
But I foresee nothing
but disaster for you

1234
01:05:23,400 --> 01:05:24,600
and this country

1235
01:05:25,200 --> 01:05:26,600
if we don't.

1236
01:05:27,100 --> 01:05:29,400
If we escalate this war,

1237
01:05:30,400 --> 01:05:33,300
I believe we'll ruin us

1238
01:05:33,400 --> 01:05:35,600
And I believe we'll ruin you

1239
01:05:36,200 --> 01:05:39,200
And all the good you've started to do

1240
01:05:48,100 --> 01:05:52,800
Shit. It's a hot one already.

1241
01:05:53,600 --> 01:05:55,900
You wish you were back in Texas,
Mr. President?

1242
01:05:56,000 --> 01:05:59,800
Fellahs, right now I'd rather
be on the moon.

1243
01:06:07,000 --> 01:06:08,200
Okay, Bob.

1244
01:06:10,500 --> 01:06:11,100
Mr. President,

1245
01:06:11,200 --> 01:06:14,000
Clark has suggested that
the stakes aren't there in Vietnam.

1246
01:06:14,100 --> 01:06:15,200
This is damn shocking.
Well, I...

1247
01:06:15,400 --> 01:06:17,600
Here are the stakes:

1248
01:06:17,700 --> 01:06:19,700
Number one. National Security.

1249
01:06:19,900 --> 01:06:21,800
If we back down in Vietnam

1250
01:06:21,900 --> 01:06:23,400
it will only be a matter of time

1251
01:06:23,500 --> 01:06:25,200
before we have to go
in some place else.

1252
01:06:25,300 --> 01:06:26,700
Two, the commitment's we've made

1253
01:06:26,900 --> 01:06:27,900
and the price of breaking them

1254
01:06:28,000 --> 01:06:31,000
Three,
and Our prestige before the world.

1255
01:06:31,200 --> 01:06:34,500
Could the stakes be any higher?

1256
01:06:34,600 --> 01:06:36,500
To elaborate on Point 1.,

1257
01:06:36,600 --> 01:06:40,200
if we withdraw, Laos, Cambodia,
Thailand, Burma will fall,

1258
01:06:40,300 --> 01:06:42,400
but the ripple effect
will be far greater.

1259
01:06:42,500 --> 01:06:45,400
With Communist agitation increasing
in Africa, India,

1260
01:06:45,500 --> 01:06:49,500
even Japan. We will have to give up
some bases.

1261
01:06:49,600 --> 01:06:52,500
Pakistan will move closer to China.

1262
01:06:53,100 --> 01:06:54,100
Point two,

1263
01:06:54,200 --> 01:06:57,100
our pledge is a pillar of peace
in the world

1264
01:06:57,200 --> 01:06:58,100
and if we break it,

1265
01:06:58,200 --> 01:07:00,200
our allies will lose faith in us.

