2269
02:04:53,000 --> 02:04:57,200
There he is! That's McNamara!
Over there!

2270
02:05:12,800 --> 02:05:15,400
Secretary McNamara,
on behalf of the subcommittee,

2271
02:05:15,500 --> 02:05:18,600
let me thank you
for your appearance here today.

2272
02:05:18,800 --> 02:05:23,500
I have, from the beginning,
and do today,

2273
02:05:23,600 --> 02:05:27,400
fully support the objectives
of the bombing

2274
02:05:28,000 --> 02:05:29,700
to interdict men, and supplies

2275
02:05:29,800 --> 02:05:32,800
and hinder the enemy's ability
to wage war in the South.

2276
02:05:33,700 --> 02:05:37,400
In this I am 100% behind
the Joint Chiefs,

2277
02:05:37,500 --> 02:05:41,500
Admiral Sharp, General Westmoreland,
and his commanders,

2278
02:05:41,700 --> 02:05:45,900
as they are fully aware,
and as the President is aware.

2279
02:05:46,000 --> 02:05:50,200
We are all greatly encouraged
to hear that, Mr. Secretary.

2280
02:05:50,300 --> 02:05:54,000
You are the last to testify,
as you know,

2281
02:05:54,100 --> 02:05:57,200
and the overwhelming view
from General Wheeler and the others

2282
02:05:57,300 --> 02:06:00,800
is that there has been excessive
interference from your office--

2283
02:06:01,000 --> 02:06:03,400
If I'd be permitted to finish
my statement, Senator

2284
02:06:03,600 --> 02:06:05,300
Stennis, there are copies available
outside the hearing room.

2285
02:06:05,400 --> 02:06:11,300
Our greater objective, however,
was, and remains,

2286
02:06:11,400 --> 02:06:13,000
to persuade the leaders
of North Vietnam

2287
02:06:13,200 --> 02:06:15,400
that they cannot prevail.

2288
02:06:15,900 --> 02:06:18,200
In this we have been unsuccessful.

2289
02:06:19,000 --> 02:06:21,200
This is due to the fact
that North Vietnam

2290
02:06:21,400 --> 02:06:23,100
can sustain its forces in the South

2291
02:06:23,200 --> 02:06:25,900
with a mere 100 tons
of supplies a day,

2292
02:06:26,000 --> 02:06:29,500
through corrupt elements

2293
02:06:29,600 --> 02:06:31,500
in the South Vietnamese government.

2294
02:06:32,000 --> 02:06:34,800
Out of 359 targets recommended
by the Chiefs,

2295
02:06:35,000 --> 02:06:37,400
only 57 remain unstruck.

2296
02:06:37,500 --> 02:06:42,200
Two are battery plants manufacturing
a total of 600 tons a year,

2297
02:06:42,300 --> 02:06:44,000
not enough to fill the corner
of a Sears,

2298
02:06:44,100 --> 02:06:45,500
Roebuck regional warehouse.

2299
02:06:45,700 --> 02:06:46,800
Just a moment, Mr. Secretary!

2300
02:06:46,900 --> 02:06:49,900
There's a rubber plant producing

2301
02:06:50,000 --> 02:06:52,100
The service station where
I fill my car

2302
02:06:52,300 --> 02:06:53,900
could supply
the output of this facility.

2303
02:06:54,000 --> 02:06:54,600
Excuse my interruption.

2304
02:06:54,800 --> 02:06:58,800
Hitting these targets will cost us
in pilots, planes,

2305
02:06:58,900 --> 02:07:04,300
and hard cash, and they will kill
more and more civilians.

2306
02:07:04,400 --> 02:07:06,700
The military knows this.

2307
02:07:06,800 --> 02:07:10,200
They think it's worth it. I do not.

2308
02:07:12,300 --> 02:07:13,000
Hold on!

2309
02:07:13,200 --> 02:07:14,600
You know what he did to me out there?

2310
02:07:15,200 --> 02:07:17,900
It's like sellin your house
and your son takes the buyer aside

2311
02:07:18,000 --> 02:07:20,100
and tells him there's leaks
in the basement.

2312
02:07:20,700 --> 02:07:23,000
Now Hanoi knows we're divided
and they'll never stop.

2313
02:07:24,100 --> 02:07:26,000
I've gotta get rid of
that sonovabitch.

2314
02:07:26,100 --> 02:07:28,200
You can't just get rid of him.

2315
02:07:28,300 --> 02:07:29,800
The Republicans will play up
the disunity

2316
02:07:30,000 --> 02:07:31,400
and Bobby'll have a field day.

2317
02:07:31,500 --> 02:07:33,500
Bobby's clamorin for him to resign
don't you know,

2318
02:07:33,600 --> 02:07:36,800
to go public against me for doin
what he advised!

2319
02:07:36,900 --> 02:07:39,500
Look, we'll find a job for McNamara

2320
02:07:39,600 --> 02:07:41,500
where he won't be able to snipe
at you.

2321
02:07:41,600 --> 02:07:43,800
I'll help you fill his post
with someone you can trust.

2322
02:07:43,900 --> 02:07:46,300
I'll do anything I can for you,
Mr. President.

2323
02:07:46,400 --> 02:07:48,800
But we have a reelection campaign
to start

2324
02:07:48,900 --> 02:07:52,000
and we do not have a policy
to end this war.

2325
02:07:53,900 --> 02:07:57,600
Clark, you'll do anything you can?

2326
02:08:06,500 --> 02:08:07,800
They're ready for you, Mr. President.

2327
02:08:07,900 --> 02:08:10,000
Yep. I'll be out in a minute.

2328
02:08:11,000 --> 02:08:12,000
Sit down, Bob.

2329
02:08:18,100 --> 02:08:20,400
I'm sorry you found out
from the Washington Post.

2330
02:08:20,500 --> 02:08:23,300
I'm sure Fowler told you,
or the bank people.

2331
02:08:24,000 --> 02:08:27,100
Nobody told me anything,
Mr. President. I uh,

2332
02:08:27,200 --> 02:08:28,400
mentioned to you in the spring

2333
02:08:28,600 --> 02:08:29,800
that I'd been approached
by the World Bank,

2334
02:08:29,900 --> 02:08:32,800
but I thought
if you were going to nominate me,

2335
02:08:32,900 --> 02:08:34,500
you would have said
something yourself.

2336
02:08:35,100 --> 02:08:37,600
They're doin fine work
there--humanitarian work.

2337
02:08:37,800 --> 02:08:38,900
I know that's of interest to you.

2338
02:08:39,000 --> 02:08:42,000
Yes, but only if it's what you want.

2339
02:08:42,100 --> 02:08:44,000
If I can no longer be of service...

2340
02:08:44,200 --> 02:08:48,400
Service? Who's been of more service
to me than you?

2341
02:08:48,600 --> 02:08:51,700
Why you've served longer than any
Defense Secretary in history.

2342
02:08:51,800 --> 02:08:53,600
Look what you've had
to shepherd us through.

2343
02:08:53,700 --> 02:08:57,600
The Cuban crisis, two Cuban crisis,
Berlin, Dominican,

2344
02:08:57,800 --> 02:08:59,400
Middle East. Hell,

2345
02:08:59,600 --> 02:09:01,800
that's a tough enough job
in peace time.

2346
02:09:02,000 --> 02:09:03,800
And look what you've had to deal with

2347
02:09:04,900 --> 02:09:09,100
Mr. President, my point is,

2348
02:09:09,200 --> 02:09:13,200
I don't have to leave
until you want me to leave.

2349
02:09:14,500 --> 02:09:18,200
Bob, Joe Fowler asked me
for three nominees.

2350
02:09:18,300 --> 02:09:20,800
I said I only got one McNamara.

2351
02:09:20,900 --> 02:09:23,600
There were tears in
the Treasury Secretary's eyes

2352
02:09:23,700 --> 02:09:25,800
cause he was hopin he'd be my choice.

2353
02:09:25,900 --> 02:09:28,200
And with tears in his eyes
he said he had to

2354
02:09:28,400 --> 02:09:30,000
submit three names to the bank.

2355
02:09:30,200 --> 02:09:34,100
I said, okay, it's McNamara,
McNamara, and McNamara.

2356
02:09:34,200 --> 02:09:35,400
You ask him.

2357
02:09:35,600 --> 02:09:40,000
Now, the bank directors vote today,
but it's uh,

2358
02:09:40,100 --> 02:09:41,600
it's just a formality.

2359
02:09:41,700 --> 02:09:43,300
Now, Bob,

2360
02:09:43,500 --> 02:09:47,200
I better get over to Lady Bird's
beautification awards,

2361
02:09:47,300 --> 02:09:48,500
important to her.

2362
02:09:48,600 --> 02:09:51,400
Your wife's the same
with her readin program, I know.

2363
02:09:51,600 --> 02:09:55,200
Yes, although with her condition
it's been difficult.

2364
02:09:55,300 --> 02:09:57,700
Ah, no improvements since surgery?

2365
02:09:58,300 --> 02:10:04,000
My son, uh... he has em as well.

2366
02:10:05,800 --> 02:10:08,400
You deserve whatever you want
from this government.

2367
02:10:08,600 --> 02:10:10,200
My obligation is to help you,

2368
02:10:10,800 --> 02:10:13,000
and this was within my power
to grant you.

2369
02:10:16,200 --> 02:10:19,800
People have an obligation
to the President,

2370
02:10:20,400 --> 02:10:22,000
not the other way around.

2371
02:10:28,800 --> 02:10:31,900
May your selfless service,
spent in defendin freedom

2372
02:10:32,000 --> 02:10:34,900
bring even greater rewards
in the larger work that you

2373
02:10:35,000 --> 02:10:38,000
now undertake to promote
freedom throughout the world.

2374
02:10:38,200 --> 02:10:40,700
Signed, Lyndon B. Johnson, President.

2375
02:10:46,200 --> 02:10:49,100
This is the Medal of Freedom,

2376
02:10:49,200 --> 02:10:50,500
the highest award a President

2377
02:10:50,700 --> 02:10:54,600
can bestow upon a citizen
of the United States.

2378
02:10:55,200 --> 02:10:59,400
I award it now to a loyal, brilliant,
good man,

2379
02:10:59,600 --> 02:11:02,900
Robert McNamara the very best we have.

2380
02:11:06,700 --> 02:11:08,700
Thank you, Mr. President,
this is an almost impossible

2381
02:11:08,800 --> 02:11:09,600
situation to respond to.

2382
02:11:09,700 --> 02:11:11,600
You're used to impossible situations.

2383
02:11:55,900 --> 02:11:58,200
Now, I stand here tonight to tell you

2384
02:11:58,300 --> 02:12:01,000
that I regard Bob McNamara here,

2385
02:12:01,100 --> 02:12:03,300
as not only one of the smartest,

2386
02:12:03,500 --> 02:12:06,100
but one of the most humane men I know.

2387
02:12:12,600 --> 02:12:15,300
One, put the men in.

2388
02:12:18,100 --> 02:12:21,500
Two, call up the reserves,
extend tours of duty.

2389
02:12:23,500 --> 02:12:26,400
And three, expand the bombing.

2390
02:12:38,500 --> 02:12:40,600
Mr. President, uh,

2391
02:12:42,700 --> 02:12:48,700
I cannot uh...
find the words to express

2392
02:12:48,900 --> 02:12:53,600
what lies in my heart today and uh...

2393
02:12:55,300 --> 02:12:57,600
I think I better respond
at another time.

2394
02:13:21,500 --> 02:13:22,400
Mr. Clifford

2395
02:13:23,400 --> 02:13:25,300
Mr. Clifford, does your acceptance
of the job

2396
02:13:25,400 --> 02:13:27,700
of Defense Secretary
signal your interest

2397
02:13:27,800 --> 02:13:29,200
in elected office?

2398
02:13:29,800 --> 02:13:34,300
It signals only my desire to serve
a great President

2399
02:13:34,500 --> 02:13:36,300
and a long-time friend.

2400
02:13:36,400 --> 02:13:41,300
I am 61 years old and I am sure
this will finish me off.

2401
02:13:43,700 --> 02:13:45,500
Quiet please! Quiet please!

2402
02:13:45,700 --> 02:13:46,700
Joe, Joe?

2403
02:13:46,800 --> 02:13:49,100
It's been observed that
in your views on Vietnam,

2404
02:13:49,200 --> 02:13:52,300
you've changed from dove to hawk,
which are you?

2405
02:13:52,400 --> 02:13:55,800
I am not conscious of falling
under any of those

2406
02:13:56,000 --> 02:13:57,600
ornithological divisions.

2407
02:13:57,700 --> 02:13:59,800
I'll tell you this, he's no ostrich.

2408
02:14:01,200 --> 02:14:03,900
I know of no man who will call it
as it is with such candor

2409
02:14:04,100 --> 02:14:06,200
and judgment as this man,
Clark Clifford.

2410
02:14:06,400 --> 02:14:08,600
We got a light at the end
of the tunnel now!

2411
02:14:17,900 --> 02:14:19,300
It's probably a small attack,

2412
02:14:19,400 --> 02:14:21,900
Mr. President the embassy
compound's been hit before.

2413
02:14:22,100 --> 02:14:23,500
Mr. Secretary,
it's not just the embassy,

2414
02:14:23,700 --> 02:14:25,500
the palace, legislature, airport, too

2415
02:14:31,800 --> 02:14:32,600
Secretary Rusk!

2416
02:14:32,700 --> 02:14:34,000
Put it on the speaker phone.

2417
02:14:37,300 --> 02:14:38,300
Go ahead, Ben.

2418
02:14:38,800 --> 02:14:42,300
Dean, I've got the duty officer
at the Embassy, Alan Brandt.

2419
02:14:42,500 --> 02:14:45,200
Mr. Brandt!
Mr. Brandt can you hear me?

2420
02:14:45,300 --> 02:14:47,700
They're shooting right outside,
Mr. Secretary.

2421
02:14:48,200 --> 02:14:49,700
Outside of the Embassy compound?

2422
02:14:49,800 --> 02:14:52,300
Inside! They blew through the wall,

2423
02:14:52,500 --> 02:14:53,400
they're at the doors.

2424
02:14:53,500 --> 02:14:54,800
Rostow, Casualty report.

2425
02:14:55,000 --> 02:14:57,200
Do you have something to defend
yourself with, Mr. Brandt?

2426
02:14:57,400 --> 02:15:00,300
I'm at the window! They're below me.
They see me.

2427
02:15:00,500 --> 02:15:03,000
They're looking right at me.
I've got to go, Mr. Secretary.

2428
02:15:03,100 --> 02:15:04,800
I've got to go I've got to get out
Small attack!?

2429
02:15:04,900 --> 02:15:06,300
These are desperation moves,

2430
02:15:06,500 --> 02:15:08,600
Mr. President
we've got them on the run!

2431
02:15:08,800 --> 02:15:10,300
It's not just Saigon.

2432
02:15:11,800 --> 02:15:13,500
The Vietcong have launched
surprise attacks

2433
02:15:13,700 --> 02:15:18,000
on 36 of the provincial capitals
of South Vietnam.

2434
02:15:18,100 --> 02:15:20,000
From the streets of Wai near the DMZ,

2435
02:15:20,100 --> 02:15:22,600
to the US Embassy compound in Saigon,

2436
02:15:22,700 --> 02:15:26,600
the casualty count on both sides
has been unprecedented.

2437
02:15:27,100 --> 02:15:29,000
The U.S. Military says
it is successfully

2438
02:15:29,100 --> 02:15:31,100
beating back the Vietcong attacks,

2439
02:15:31,200 --> 02:15:34,300
but clearly they are paying
an enormous price.

2440
02:15:34,500 --> 02:15:36,800
The enemy's well-laid plans
went afoul!

2441
02:15:36,900 --> 02:15:40,100
They tried to ignite a revolution
in the South, and they failed.

2442
02:15:40,300 --> 02:15:43,600
If this is a failure, God help us
when they have a success.

2443
02:16:01,400 --> 02:16:03,800
I've given em all the men,
the planes, the guns,

2444
02:16:03,900 --> 02:16:05,000
the bullets he said he needed,

2445
02:16:05,100 --> 02:16:06,900
I thought we were winnin this thing!

2446
02:16:07,000 --> 02:16:10,000
Now Westmoreland says
he wants 206,000 more troops!

2447
02:16:10,200 --> 02:16:11,900

2448
02:16:12,000 --> 02:16:13,900
We'll have 750,000 there.

2449
02:16:14,100 --> 02:16:16,800
Three quarters of a million men
in Vietnam.

2450
02:16:16,900 --> 02:16:19,400
Light at the end of the tunnel!
Hell, we don't even have a tunnel!

2451
02:16:19,500 --> 02:16:21,400
We don't even know
where the tunnel is!

2452
02:16:21,500 --> 02:16:22,900
I want you to get Westmoreland here,

2453
02:16:23,000 --> 02:16:25,000
get your people together
and look at this thing.

2454
02:16:25,200 --> 02:16:26,500
We'll give em the boys if we have to,

2455
02:16:26,600 --> 02:16:27,900
but on your recommendation.

2456
02:16:28,100 --> 02:16:29,100
You'll wait?

2457
02:16:29,200 --> 02:16:31,000
I'll wait, but not for long.

2458
02:16:31,100 --> 02:16:33,900
If he needs em what the hell
am I supposed to do!?

2459
02:16:34,900 --> 02:16:38,500
Old friend... get me an answer.

2460
02:16:39,200 --> 02:16:42,000
Give us these troops
and we can seize the initiative!

2461
02:16:42,100 --> 02:16:43,500
But it will just be more of the same!

2462
02:16:43,600 --> 02:16:45,900
The enemy's taken 200,000 killed

2463
02:16:46,100 --> 02:16:47,300
and he'll take 200,000 more!

2464
02:16:47,400 --> 02:16:48,500
We've lost a tenth that many

2465
02:16:48,700 --> 02:16:50,100
and Americans are rioting
in the streets.

2466
02:16:50,300 --> 02:16:52,800
They should be cheering!
They Vietcong lost.

2467
02:16:52,900 --> 02:16:54,200
We were victorious.

2468
02:16:54,400 --> 02:16:54,800
That's true, Walt,

2469
02:16:55,000 --> 02:16:57,100
but remember they only committed

2470
02:16:57,300 --> 02:17:00,000
to this offensive--holding
enough back to strike again.

2471
02:17:00,100 --> 02:17:02,000
That's right, damn it
and it could happen at any time.

2472
02:17:02,100 --> 02:17:03,700
I say put the men in.

2473
02:17:03,900 --> 02:17:05,900
There are no more trained men.

2474
02:17:06,100 --> 02:17:09,000
We would ship raw troops and train
them in the rear.

2475
02:17:09,200 --> 02:17:12,300
What rear? There is no rear
in Vietnam anymore.

2476
02:17:12,400 --> 02:17:15,100
I would hope we've at least learned
that from this victory.

2477
02:17:15,200 --> 02:17:18,500
With 206,000 more men we could go
into Laos, Cambodia,

2478
02:17:18,700 --> 02:17:21,100
North Vietnam and cut out
their supply routes once

2479
02:17:21,200 --> 02:17:24,100
and for all we have never been given
that authority!

2480
02:17:24,800 --> 02:17:28,700
Excuse me, General. Dean,
you said the enemy

2481
02:17:28,900 --> 02:17:32,200
committed 175,000 men
to the offensive.

2482
02:17:32,400 --> 02:17:33,300
That's right, Clark.

2483
02:17:33,500 --> 02:17:35,200
And General Westmoreland says
that they suffered

2484
02:17:35,300 --> 02:17:38,800
to wounded ratio.

2485
02:17:38,900 --> 02:17:40,300
It's right here in my report.

2486
02:17:40,500 --> 02:17:42,700
We beat the pants off them!

2487
02:17:43,300 --> 02:17:46,000
Then how in the hell can we justify
to the public sending

2488
02:17:46,100 --> 02:17:47,900
hundreds of thousands more men!?

2489
02:17:48,000 --> 02:17:49,800
We tell them this:

2490
02:17:49,900 --> 02:17:53,500
that we're within inches
of victory inches!

2491
02:17:53,700 --> 02:17:56,000

2492
02:17:56,700 --> 02:17:57,400
Yes, sir.

2493
02:17:57,500 --> 02:18:00,400
And 3.5 times that number
are out of action?

2494
02:18:00,600 --> 02:18:01,500
It's in the report, Clark.

2495
02:18:01,600 --> 02:18:05,900
If there's 45,000 dead and three
and a half times that number...

2496
02:18:06,000 --> 02:18:07,600

2497
02:18:07,700 --> 02:18:12,500

2498
02:18:13,100 --> 02:18:17,800
General, according to you
and General Westmoreland

2499
02:18:17,900 --> 02:18:23,100
we have killed and wounded 120%
of the enemy.

2500
02:18:28,600 --> 02:18:31,100
It's becoming more and more evident

2501
02:18:31,200 --> 02:18:33,800
that an out and out military victory

2502
02:18:33,900 --> 02:18:36,500
cannot be achieved with any strategy.

2503
02:18:38,500 --> 02:18:42,800
So... these are my recommendations:

2504
02:18:43,300 --> 02:18:46,100
one, send Westmoreland
only those forces

2505
02:18:46,300 --> 02:18:48,600
that will satisfy his immediate need.

2506
02:18:48,800 --> 02:18:51,400
Wheeler has agreed to 22,000 plus

2507
02:18:51,500 --> 02:18:52,800
the units previously approved

2508
02:18:52,900 --> 02:18:55,000
and already scheduled for deployment.

2509
02:18:55,100 --> 02:18:57,400
This would stave off immediate defeat

2510
02:18:57,500 --> 02:18:59,800
while we move to negotiations.

2511
02:19:00,300 --> 02:19:01,900
We realize that the settlemen

2512
02:19:02,000 --> 02:19:03,800
will not be favorable for Saigon

